&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Why Choose Bottomline?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to transform the way businesses pay and get paid? Bottomline is a global leader in business payments and cash management, with over 35 years of experience and moving more than $16 trillion in payments annually. We&#39;re looking for passionate individuals to join our team and help drive impactful results for our customers. If you&#39;re dedicated to delighting customers and promoting growth and innovation - we want you on our team!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Agile Delivery Manager&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Agile Delivery Manager&amp;nbsp;is responsible for&amp;nbsp;driving predictable, high‑quality delivery across multiple Scrum teams within the Paymode platform. This role works closely with Product, Engineering, QA, Finance, and external vendors to ensure delivery excellence, release readiness, and strong operational discipline.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;They oversee multiple teams/pods, provide hands‑on delivery leadership when needed, and co-own release management, metrics, vendor coordination, and cross‑functional alignment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;This position is ideal for a senior delivery professional who combines servant leadership with strong operational rigor and can&amp;nbsp;operate&amp;nbsp;effectively at the team, release, and organizational levels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based at our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Bangalore&lt;/strong&gt;, India office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agile Team &amp;amp; Pod Delivery Oversight&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee delivery health across multiple Scrum teams and pods, adjusting involvement based on team maturity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach Scrum Masters and Delivery Leads, including 1:1 support as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a mediator for friction, capacity constraints, and delivery risks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain oversight of maintenance-only and production-support teams, ensuring scope discipline.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure capacity alignment with Product and Engineering leadership.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Release Management &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-own end-to-end release responsibilities including:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Release planning,&amp;nbsp;kickoff, and facilitation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Release deck creation, updates, and stakeholder communication&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Release retrospectives and action tracking&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participation in Release Command&amp;nbsp;Center&amp;nbsp;rotations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as backup host for sprint reviews or release ceremonies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce release best practices, communication, and escalation standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Release Planning, Metrics &amp;amp; Insights&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;release capacity plans for feature teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform velocity analysis and&amp;nbsp;identify&amp;nbsp;delivery risks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate staffing, roster changes, and security&amp;nbsp;component&amp;nbsp;rotations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and&amp;nbsp;analyze&amp;nbsp;release progress using Jira

