&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Why Choose Bottomline?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to transform the way businesses pay and get paid? Bottomline is a global leader in business payments and cash management, with over 35 years of experience and moving more than $16 trillion in payments annually. We&#39;re looking for passionate individuals to join our team and help drive impactful results for our customers. If you&#39;re dedicated to delighting customers and promoting growth and innovation - we want you on our team!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Business Systems/Solutions Analyst for our Revenue &amp;amp; Customer Systems Products, directly aligned with our Manager of Revenue &amp;amp; Customer Systems. This role partners closely with stakeholders across Sales, Finance, Customer Support and Operations to translate business needs into scalable system solutions. The ideal candidate brings a strong analytical mindset, and an interest in learning complex systems and business processes through expert use &amp;amp; knowledge of the Salesforce platform and related systems. Essential Job Functions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Gather, document, and refine business requirements into user stories with clear acceptance criteria&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Own and manage backlog items, ensuring readiness for sprint planning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Partner with technical teams to translate requirements into functional solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Support end-to-end delivery across the SDLC (intake → build → test → release)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Support CPQ processes including product configuration, pricing, quoting, and approvals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Collaborate with stakeholders to improve quote accuracy, pricing logic, and commercial workflows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Analyze and troubleshoot issues in quote-to-cash processes across Salesforce, CPQ, and downstream systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Assist in defining standardized processes across regions and business units&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build strong relationships with Sales, Product, Finance Ops, and Customer teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Facilitate working sessions to identify pain points and improvement opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Communicate progress, risks, and outcomes clearly to both technical and business audiences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Participate in demos and stakeholder reviews of delivered functionality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Actively participate in agile ceremonies (stand-ups, sprint planning, refinement)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Support testing efforts (UAT coordination, defect tracking, validation)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Remove blockers and ensure smooth team execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Contribute to continuous improvement of processes and documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 2–4 years of experience as a Business Analyst, Systems Analyst, or similar role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Experience working within Salesforce (Sales Cloud and Service Cloud)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Exposure to CPQ tools such as Salesforce CPQ, Apttus/Conga, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Strong skills in requirements gathering, documentation, and stakeholder communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience working in Agile or Scrum environments Preferred Skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Hands-on experience supporting CPQ implementations or enhancements; Salesforce admin/config experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Salesforce Certification (Admin or Business Analyst)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Understanding of quote-to-cash, order management, or revenue processes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• Experience working with integrated systems (e.g., ERP, billing platforms)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Familiarity with project and documentation management tools like Jira, Confluence, or similar&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education and Experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;• 2-4 years of experience; plus, Salesforce platform experience.&lt;/p&gt;
